The paper deals with the capacity and error exponents of steganographic systems, which are related to information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the security and detection of hidden messages, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of watermarking codes and binning methods suggests a focus on multimedia security (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the use of linear codes, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the discussion of computational security suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
